/ The report body lives in a turbo-frame with no markup src — so it never
/ eager-loads and never self-references (a frame whose src is its own page
/ is rejected by Turbo). While the report is in progress the load-poll
/ Stimulus controller (inside _report) sets the frame's src on its first
/ tick and reload()s it thereafter, replacing the body with freshly
/ rendered content until the report reaches a terminal status.
/
/ target: '_top' makes descendant links (the per-row "Work" links, the
/ loader subtitle link) drive a full-page visit rather than navigating
/ inside the frame — without it Turbo looks for a matching load_report
/ frame in the linked page, doesn't find one, and renders "content
/ missing". The poller is unaffected: it calls reload()/src= on the frame
/ element directly, which target does not govern.
- if @load_report.previewing?
  / XML and multipage loads pause here: render the preview (no poll frame —
  / there is no background job running until the librarian confirms).
  = render (@loader.multipage? ? 'multipage_preview' : 'preview'), load_report: @load_report, loader: @loader, preview: @preview
- else
  = turbo_frame_tag 'load_report', target: '_top' do
    = render 'report', load_report: @load_report, loader: @loader
